==English==

===Verb===
'''[[eat]] [[one's]] [[hat]]'''

# {{idiom}}  Used in a [[result clause]] to express [[disbelief]] in the [[conditional clause]] proposition.
#: ''If England signs into the European single currency before 2008, I'll '''eat my hat'''.''
#: ''He said he would '''eat his hat''' if more than ten people came. He'd better fetch a knife and fork!''

